Revision history for App-SCM-Digest

0.14    20 October 2024
        - Set the default branch name for Git operations (RT #156205).
        - Update the Git pull command to merge by default.

0.13    5 November 2017
        - Fix wrong skip test counts.

0.12    2 November 2017
        - Re-clone the repository if an attempted operation fails,
          and restore the original repository if the re-clone or
          retried operation doesn't succeed.
        - Prefer the remote repository when merging conflicts.
        - Handle missing commits better.

0.11    13 February 2016
        - Catch 'init-db' errors in tests.
        - Set user.name and user.email for Git repository clones in
          tests.
        - Fix wrong skip test count.

0.10    10 Februry 2016
        - Take account of 'ignore_errors' in get_email.
        - Fix file-handling problems.

0.09    30 January 2016
        - Set user.name and user.email for Git repositories created in
          tests.

0.08    7 January 2016
        - Fix wrong test skip count.

0.07    6 January 2016
        - Add an 'ignore_errors' configuration option.
        - Simplify 'init-db' usage in tests, so that they work when
          using older versions of Git.

0.06    16 December 2015
        - Fix file handle leak.

0.05    26 November 2015
        - Fix wrong test skip count.
        - Use 'init-db' instead of 'init' for Git tests, so that they
          work when using older versions of Git.

0.04    21 November 2015
        - Fix debug output problem, and print output whenever a
          problem occurs.

0.03    22 October 2015
        - Do not assume that the 'master' branch exists for Git
          repositories, when removing local branches that no longer
          have corresponding remote branches.

0.02    21 October 2015
        - Fix commit ordering problem.
        - Remove local branches that no longer exist in the remote
          repository.
        - Set dummy user when ui.username is not set, in Mercurial
          tests (Syohei Yoshida).

0.01    18 October 2015
        - Initial release.
